      "id": 359563,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>A problem often encountered in the oxidation of primary alcohols to carboxylic acids is that esters are sometimes produced as by-products. For example, oxidation of ethanol yields acetic acid and ethyl acetate:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ0lXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--cc8cb8d5e9fd84e7f9b5c87a2c149073d3233680/OChem_17_EC_050.jpg\" alt=\"Ethanol reacts with chromium trioxide to form acetic acid and ethylacetate.\">\n<p>Propose a mechanism to account for the formation of ethyl acetate. Take into account the reversible reaction between aldehydes and alcohols:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ01XIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0be128f588529ad237bb6e67c097dc10ad696be4/OChem_17_EC_051.jpg\" alt=\"An aldehyde, R C H O reacts with R dash O H to form carbon linked to H , R, O H and O R dash group.\">",
